<br>
People pay that much for their broadband per month just so they can run two computers and play EQ on two computers (on two different accounts).<br>
<br>
The arch-typical &quot;uber guilds&quot; like FoH are people that can (and do) play EQ in place of having jobs.  I have no idea how they manage it - they could be school age, be independently wealthy, be sitting at home on disability, who knows?<br>
<br>
The point is that those types of folks really don't care about $40/month as opposed to $10/month.  That's what, less than a buck and a half per day?  So they don't get that candy bar and coke from the vending machine.<br>
<br>
Some have been speculating that only older folks with good jobs would be able to afford the extra price.  I submit the opposite - people with jobs would be less likely to buy into the idea because they play less and would have a harder time justifying the extra expense to their scowling spouses.  You'll get a higher proportion of teenagers on such a server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dawgtide>dawgtide</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/3/02 6:37:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1259.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> reply</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Henk here.  While I may just go check it out cause I can afford it, I see it as a major league level 60 server.  I imagine there will be so much arguing about the big targets it will be unbelievable.  I actually think this is funny for one reason.  I would love to see all the big guilds go there and then race to open the sleeper and stuff like that.  I think it would be hilarious myself.  Especially if they made it where you could not leave with your gear.  Maybe it is just me, but I think this could happen.  I imagine most of the power guys are college kids with much more time.  Heck if this game would have been out when I was in school, I might could have been one myself.  But one thing I do not see is high schoolers being plentiful.  If there are a lot of parents willing to spend that on their kids for a game each month, then we have too many spoiled kids.  I had to work and I learned about valuing money.  That is not the way my folks would have brought me up.  I could be wrong but that is my opinion.<br>
